The paper deals with the problem of transferring knowledge from one domain to another, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method involves disentangling features, which is a common technique in unsupervised learning (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also mentions medical imaging, which falls under the sub-category of computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) for text-based medical records.
